4. Combat Action Taxonomy

The library defines six primary action classes.

4.1 Movement Actions

Used for non-combat chess movement.

Examples:

Chess Event	Cinematic Action
Pawn advance	formation advance
Knight movement	teleport dash
Bishop movement	energy glide
Rook movement	battlefield march
Queen movement	royal movement
King movement	tactical retreat

Example:

{
"type":"movement",

"action":
"teleport_dash",

"style":
"assassin"
}
4.2 Attack Actions

Used for offensive interactions.

Chess Event	Action
Pawn capture	soldier strike
Knight capture	assassination
Bishop capture	energy blade
Rook capture	heavy impact
Queen capture	ultimate execution
King capture	desperate attack
4.3 Defensive Actions

Used for protection.

Chess Event	Action
Block	shield formation
Castle	fortress deployment
King move	survival maneuver
4.4 Special Actions

Rare strategic moments.

Chess Event	Action
Sacrifice	heroic last stand
Promotion	evolution
Fork	combo attack
Pin	immobilization
Skewer	penetration attack
4.5 Victory Actions
Event	Cinematic Result
Checkmate	final execution
Resignation	surrender scene
Timeout	collapse scene
